@startuml Mapped_Sequence_Diagrams
' Mapped - Sequence Diagrams (PlantUML)
' 5 main usage scenarios for the Mapped microservices architecture
' Standard: UML 2.0

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam backgroundColor #F5F5F5
skinparam actorBackgroundColor #7C3AED
skinparam actorBorderColor #5B21B6
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #2D2D44
skinparam participantBorderColor #7C3AED
skinparam participantFontColor #FFFFFF
skinparam noteBkgColor #FFF9E6
skinparam noteBorderColor #FFA500

' Scenario 1: Creating a post linked to a place with media

@startuml Mapped_Sequence_Diagram_1

== Scenario 1: Create Post with Place and Media ==

actor User as User1
participant "Frontend\n(React)" as Frontend1
participant "API Gateway" as API1
participant "Posts Service" as Posts1
participant "Places Service" as Places1
participant "Media Service" as Media1
participant "Database" as DB1
participant "File Storage" as FS1

User1 -> Frontend1: 1. Open post creation form
Frontend1 -> Frontend1: 2. Load image locally
User1 -> Frontend1: 3. Enter post content and select place
Frontend1 -> API1: 4. POST /media/upload (file)
API1 -> Media1: 5. UploadFile(file, userID)
Media1 -> FS1: 6. Save file
FS1 --> Media1: 7. Return media URL
Media1 -> DB1: 8. SaveMediaFile(url, name, size, userID)
DB1 --> Media1: 9. OK, ID = 123
Media1 --> API1: 10. {url, id}
API1 --> Frontend1: 11. 200 OK {mediaURL}
Frontend1 -> API1: 12. POST /posts/create {content, mediaURLs[], placeID}
API1 -> Posts1: 13. CreatePost(userID, username, req)
Posts1 -> Posts1: 14. Validate (content not empty)
Posts1 -> Places1: 15. GetPlace(placeID, userID)
Places1 -> DB1: 16. SELECT Place WHERE id = placeID
DB1 --> Places1: 17. Place {id, name, rating}
Places1 --> Posts1: 18. Place OK
Posts1 -> DB1: 19. INSERT Post {userID, username, content, mediaURLs, placeID}
DB1 --> Posts1: 20. OK, postID = 456
Posts1 -> DB1: 21. UPDATE Place SET LikeCount + 1 WHERE id = placeID
DB1 --> Posts1: 22. OK
Posts1 --> API1: 23. {postID, createdAt}
API1 --> Frontend1: 24. 201 Created {post}
Frontend1 --> User1: 25. Success: Post created!

@enduml Mapped_Sequence_Diagram_1

' Scenario 2: Like place and create review with rating

@startuml Mapped_Sequence_Diagram_2

== Scenario 2: Like Place and Create Review with Media ==

actor User as User2
participant "Frontend\n(React)" as Frontend2
participant "API Gateway" as API2
participant "Places Service" as Places2
participant "Reviews Service" as Reviews2
participant "Media Service" as Media2
participant "Database" as DB2
participant "File Storage" as FS2

User2 -> Frontend2: 1. Open place page
Frontend2 -> API2: 2. GET /places/{placeID}
API2 -> Places2: 3. GetPlace(placeID, userID)
Places2 -> DB2: 4. SELECT Place WHERE id = placeID
DB2 --> Places2: 5. Place {name, rating, reviewCount}
Places2 --> API2: 6. PlaceResponse
API2 --> Frontend2: 7. 200 OK {place, liked, disliked}
Frontend2 --> User2: 8. Display place information

User2 -> Frontend2: 9. Click like on place
Frontend2 -> API2: 10. POST /places/{placeID}/like {type: like}
API2 -> Places2: 11. LikePlace(placeID, userID, type)
Places2 -> DB2: 12. INSERT PlaceLike {placeID, userID, type}
DB2 --> Places2: 13. OK, likeID = 789
Places2 -> DB2: 14. UPDATE Place SET LikeCount = LikeCount + 1
DB2 --> Places2: 15. OK
Places2 --> API2: 16. {likeID, success}
API2 --> Frontend2: 17. 201 Created
Frontend2 --> User2: 18. Success: Place liked!

User2 -> Frontend2: 19. Fill review form (rating 4.5, text, photo)
Frontend2 -> Frontend2: 20. Load review photo locally
Frontend2 -> API2: 21. POST /media/upload {photo}
API2 -> Media2: 22. UploadFile(file, userID)
Media2 -> FS2: 23. Save image
FS2 --> Media2: 24. Return URL
Media2 -> DB2: 25. SaveMediaFile(url)
DB2 --> Media2: 26. OK
Media2 --> API2: 27. {url}
API2 --> Frontend2: 28. 200 OK

Frontend2 -> API2: 29. POST /reviews/create {placeID, rating: 4.5, content, mediaURLs}
API2 -> Reviews2: 30. CreateReview(userID, username, req)
Reviews2 -> Reviews2: 31. Validate (rating 0-5, content less than 5000 chars)
Reviews2 -> DB2: 32. INSERT Review {placeID, userID, rating, content, mediaURLs}
DB2 --> Reviews2: 33. OK, reviewID = 111
Reviews2 -> Places2: 34. UpdatePlaceRating(placeID, newRating)
Places2 -> DB2: 35. SELECT AVG(rating) FROM Review WHERE placeID = ?
DB2 --> Places2: 36. avgRating = 4.3
Places2 -> DB2: 37. UPDATE Place SET Rating = 4.3, ReviewCount = ReviewCount + 1
DB2 --> Places2: 38. OK
Places2 --> Reviews2: 39. OK
Reviews2 --> API2: 40. {reviewID, createdAt}
API2 --> Frontend2: 41. 201 Created {review}
Frontend2 --> User2: 42. Success: Review published!

@enduml Mapped_Sequence_Diagram_2

' Scenario 3: Search nearby places and view details

@startuml Mapped_Sequence_Diagram_3

== Scenario 3: Geo-Search Nearby Places and View Reviews ==

actor User as User3
participant "Frontend\n(React)" as Frontend3
participant "API Gateway" as API3
participant "Places Service" as Places3
participant "Reviews Service" as Reviews3
participant "Database" as DB3

User3 -> Frontend3: 1. Open map with current location
Frontend3 -> Frontend3: 2. Get GPS coordinates (lat: 55.75, lng: 37.62)

Frontend3 -> API3: 3. GET /places/nearby?lat=55.75&lng=37.62&radius=5km
API3 -> Places3: 4. GetNearbyPlaces(lat, lng, radius, userID)
Places3 -> DB3: 5. SELECT * FROM Place WHERE distance(lat,lng) less than radius
DB3 --> Places3: 6. [Place1, Place2, Place3, ..., Place10]
Places3 -> Places3: 7. Sort by rating
Places3 --> API3: 8. []PlaceResponse {place, liked, disliked}
API3 --> Frontend3: 9. 200 OK {places[]}
Frontend3 --> User3: 10. Display 10 places on map

User3 -> Frontend3: 11. Click on place (placeID = 456)
Frontend3 -> API3: 12. GET /places/{placeID}
API3 -> Places3: 13. GetPlace(placeID, userID)
Places3 -> DB3: 14. SELECT Place WHERE id = 456
DB3 --> Places3: 15. Place {name, desc, rating, reviewCount}
Places3 --> API3: 16. PlaceResponse
API3 --> Frontend3: 17. 200 OK {place}
Frontend3 --> User3: 18. Open place card with details

User3 -> Frontend3: 19. Scroll to reviews and click View All
Frontend3 -> API3: 20. GET /places/{placeID}/reviews?limit=10&offset=0
API3 -> Reviews3: 21. GetPlaceReviews(placeID, limit, offset)
Reviews3 -> DB3: 22. SELECT * FROM Review WHERE placeID = 456 LIMIT 10 OFFSET 0
DB3 --> Reviews3: 23. [Review1, Review2, ..., Review10]
Reviews3 -> Reviews3: 24. Add user info (username, avatar)
Reviews3 --> API3: 25. []Review {content, rating, createdAt, author}
API3 --> Frontend3: 26. 200 OK {reviews[]}
Frontend3 --> User3: 27. Display all reviews with ratings

User3 -> Frontend3: 28. Mark as place viewed
Frontend3 -> API3: 29. POST /places/{placeID}/view {timestamp}
API3 -> Places3: 30. RecordPlaceView(placeID, userID)
Places3 -> DB3: 31. INSERT PlaceView {placeID, userID, viewedAt}
DB3 --> Places3: 32. OK
Places3 --> API3: 33. {success}
API3 --> Frontend3: 34. 201 Created
Frontend3 --> User3: 35. Success: View recorded

@enduml Mapped_Sequence_Diagram_3

' Scenario 4: Registration, login and profile update

@startuml Mapped_Sequence_Diagram_4

== Scenario 4: Registration, Authentication and Profile ==

actor User as User4
participant "Frontend\n(React)" as Frontend4
participant "API Gateway" as API4
participant "Auth Service" as Auth4
participant "Database" as DB4
participant "Media Service" as Media4
participant "File Storage" as FS4

User4 -> Frontend4: 1. Open registration page
User4 -> Frontend4: 2. Enter email, username, password
Frontend4 -> API4: 3. POST /auth/register {email, username, password}
API4 -> Auth4: 4. Register(req: RegisterRequest)
Auth4 -> Auth4: 5. Validate (email not empty, password 8+ chars)
Auth4 -> DB4: 6. SELECT User WHERE email = ?
DB4 --> Auth4: 7. No results (email available)
Auth4 -> Auth4: 8. Hash password (bcrypt)
Auth4 -> DB4: 9. INSERT User {email, username, hashedPassword, role: user}
DB4 --> Auth4: 10. OK, userID = 789
Auth4 -> Auth4: 11. Generate JWT token {userID, role, exp}
Auth4 --> API4: 12. AuthResponse {token, user{userID, username, role}}
API4 --> Frontend4: 13. 201 Created {token}
Frontend4 -> Frontend4: 14. Save token in localStorage
Frontend4 --> User4: 15. Success: Registration complete! Go to home

User4 -> Frontend4: 16. (Login) Open login form
User4 -> Frontend4: 17. Enter email and password
Frontend4 -> API4: 18. POST /auth/login {email, password}
API4 -> Auth4: 19. Login(req: LoginRequest)
Auth4 -> DB4: 20. SELECT User WHERE email = ?
DB4 --> Auth4: 21. User {userID, username, hashedPassword, role}
Auth4 -> Auth4: 22. Compare password (bcrypt.CompareHashAndPassword)
Auth4 -> Auth4: 23. OK: Passwords match
Auth4 -> Auth4: 24. Generate new JWT token
Auth4 --> API4: 25. AuthResponse {token, user}
API4 --> Frontend4: 26. 200 OK {token}
Frontend4 -> Frontend4: 27. Update localStorage with new token
Frontend4 --> User4: 28. Success: Login complete!

User4 -> Frontend4: 29. Open profile (My Profile)
Frontend4 -> API4: 30. GET /auth/profile (with Authorization: Bearer token)
API4 -> Auth4: 31. GetUserByID(userID) + ValidateToken(token)
Auth4 -> DB4: 32. SELECT User WHERE id = userID
DB4 --> Auth4: 33. User {id, email, username, avatar, bio}
Auth4 --> API4: 34. User
API4 --> Frontend4: 35. 200 OK {user}
Frontend4 --> User4: 36. Display profile (avatar, bio, email)

User4 -> Frontend4: 37. Update avatar (upload new photo)
Frontend4 -> API4: 38. POST /media/upload {file}
API4 -> Media4: 39. UploadFile(file, userID)
Media4 -> FS4: 40. Save file
FS4 --> Media4: 41. URL = /media/user_789_avatar.jpg
Media4 -> DB4: 42. SaveMediaFile(url, userID)
DB4 --> Media4: 43. OK
Media4 --> API4: 44. {url}
API4 --> Frontend4: 45. 200 OK {mediaURL}

Frontend4 -> API4: 46. PUT /auth/profile {avatar, bio}
API4 -> Auth4: 47. UpdateUser(userID, req)
Auth4 -> DB4: 48. UPDATE User SET avatar = ?, bio = ? WHERE id = ?
DB4 --> Auth4: 49. OK
Auth4 --> API4: 50. User {updated}
API4 --> Frontend4: 51. 200 OK {user}
Frontend4 --> User4: 52. Success: Profile updated!

@enduml Mapped_Sequence_Diagram_4

' Scenario 5: Create group, add members and chat

@startuml Mapped_Sequence_Diagram_5

== Scenario 5: Create Group, Chat and Message Exchange ==

actor "User 1\n(Owner)" as User5A
participant "Frontend 1" as Frontend5A
participant "API Gateway" as API5
participant "Places Service" as Places5
participant "Chat Service" as Chat5
participant "Database" as DB5
actor "User 2\n(Member)" as User5B
participant "Frontend 2" as Frontend5B

User5A -> Frontend5A: 1. Open group creation form
User5A -> Frontend5A: 2. Enter group name and description
Frontend5A -> API5: 3. POST /places/groups/create {name, description}
API5 -> Places5: 4. CreateGroup(ownerID, req)
Places5 -> DB5: 5. INSERT Group {ownerID, name, description}
DB5 --> Places5: 6. OK, groupID = 999
Places5 -> DB5: 7. INSERT GroupMember {groupID, userID, role: owner}
DB5 --> Places5: 8. OK
Places5 --> API5: 9. {groupID, name}
API5 --> Frontend5A: 10. 201 Created {group}
Frontend5A --> User5A: 11. Success: Group created! ID = 999

User5A -> Frontend5A: 12. Click Invite Members
Frontend5A -> API5: 13. POST /places/groups/{groupID}/add-member {targetUserID}
API5 -> Places5: 14. AddGroupMember(groupID, requesterID, targetUserID)
Places5 -> DB5: 15. SELECT Group WHERE id = groupID AND ownerID = requesterID
DB5 --> Places5: 16. OK (check permissions)
Places5 -> DB5: 17. INSERT GroupMember {groupID, userID: targetUserID, role: member}
DB5 --> Places5: 18. OK
Places5 --> API5: 19. {success}
API5 --> Frontend5A: 20. 201 Created
Frontend5A --> User5A: 21. Success: Member added!

User5A -> Frontend5A: 22. Open group chat (group 999)
Frontend5A -> API5: 23. GET /chat/group/{groupID}/messages?limit=50
API5 -> Chat5: 24. GetMessages(chatID, limit)
Chat5 -> DB5: 25. SELECT * FROM ChatMessage WHERE chatID = ? ORDER BY createdAt DESC
DB5 --> Chat5: 26. []ChatMessage
Chat5 --> API5: 27. []ChatMessage
API5 --> Frontend5A: 28. 200 OK {messages[]}
Frontend5A --> User5A: 29. Load chat history

User5A -> Frontend5A: 30. Enter message with photo
Frontend5A -> API5: 31. POST /media/upload {photo}
API5 -> Places5: 32. UploadFile(file, userID)
Places5 --> API5: 33. {mediaURL}
API5 --> Frontend5A: 34. 200 OK

Frontend5A -> API5: 35. POST /chat/{chatID}/send {text, attachments[]}
API5 -> Chat5: 36. SendMessage(chatID, userID, text)
Chat5 -> DB5: 37. INSERT ChatMessage {chatID, userID, username, text}
DB5 --> Chat5: 38. OK, messageID = 555
Chat5 -> DB5: 39. INSERT MessageAttachment {messageID, url, type}
DB5 --> Chat5: 40. OK
Chat5 --> API5: 41. {messageID, createdAt}
API5 --> Frontend5A: 42. 201 Created
Frontend5A --> User5A: 43. Success: Message sent!

Frontend5A -> Frontend5A: 44. WebSocket: Broadcast message to others in chat
Frontend5B -> Frontend5B: 45. WebSocket: Receive new message
Frontend5B --> User5B: 46. New message: User1: Text + photo

User5B -> Frontend5B: 47. Reply to message
Frontend5B -> API5: 48. POST /chat/{chatID}/send {text: Reply}
API5 -> Chat5: 49. SendMessage(chatID, User2ID, Reply)
Chat5 -> DB5: 50. INSERT ChatMessage
DB5 --> Chat5: 51. OK, messageID = 556
Chat5 --> API5: 52. {success}
API5 --> Frontend5B: 53. 201 Created
Frontend5B --> User5B: 54. Success: Reply sent!

Frontend5B -> Frontend5B: 55. WebSocket: Broadcast reply to User1
Frontend5A -> Frontend5A: 56. WebSocket: Receive reply
Frontend5A --> User5A: 57. User2 replied: Reply

@enduml Mapped_Sequence_Diagram_5
